Title: On Target-Space Duality in p-Branes

Authors: R. Percacci and E. Sezgin

Comments: 12 pages, plain TEX, SISSA 44/94/EP, CTP-TAMU-15/94

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A10 (1995) 441-450

We study the target-space duality transformations in $p$--branes astransformations which mix the worldvolume field equations with Bianchiidentities. We consider an $(m+p+1)$-dimensional spacetime with $p+1$dimensions compactified, and a particular form of the background fields. Wefind that while a $GL(2)=SL(2)\times R$ group is realized when $m=0$, only atwo parameter group is realized when $m>0$.